    ## Experience
    - **Research assistant** at Ghent University since 2019.
        Pursuing a PhD in Computer Science. Building **[Dolos](https://dolos.ugent.be)**, a source code plagiarism detection tool. [List of publications](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=-v9IEX4AAAAJ).

      Contributor to the programming exercise platform **[Dodona](https://dodona.be)** and the metagenomics analysis tool **[UMGAP](https://github.com/unipept/umgap)**.



    - **Teacher** of topics in [Computer Science](https://informatica.ugent.be/).
      - Algorithms (Java, C)
      - Object Oriented Programming (Java)
      - Scripting (Python)

    - **Cybersecurity adept**. Winner of the Cyber Security Challenge
      Belgium 2019 and part of the **national team** in the European Cyber
      Security Challenge 2018 (London).

    - **Algorithm developer** as an intern at [Comsof](https://comsof.com/),
      a fiber network planning company. Developed specialised algorithms to optimize communication networks.

    - **Chair** and **systems administrator** of the student hacker space
      [Zeus WPI](https://zeus.gent). Building and hacking on awesome projects together, fostering a community of creativity and cooperation.

